SIMPLE: measly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: measly
<hw>mea"sly</hw> <pr>(m⟦emac⟧"zly)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Infected with measles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Containing larval tapeworms; --
said of pork and beef.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Contemptibly small in quantity; meager; absurdly
insufficient or bad; <as>as, a <ex>measly</ex> few dollars for all that
work</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>measurability</ent>⟦br⟧
